NAME
	llm-recorder (service) - enumerate numeric subdirectories of a mount, sample a usage and a model file from each, and rewrite an index plus per-id current/history files

INTERFACE
	service (MatrixService)

READS
	.		the mount directory (e.g. /mnt/llm): entries whose
			names are all digits are taken as session ids
	<id>/usage	text "estimated/limit" (two ints split on '/')
	<id>/model	model name string

WRITES	(to its outdir /tmp/matrix/llm-recorder/ - a consumer mounts it there)
	sessions	one session id per line (ids currently visible)
	<id>/current	single line: ms model tokens limit
	<id>/history	one line per ring sample: ms tokens limit,
			oldest first (60-sample ring)

DESCRIPTION
	1000 ms poll.  All writes are atomic (tmp file + rename), so
	readers see old, new, or briefly no file - never torn.  Sessions
	absent from the source vanish from the index on the next poll;
	their stale outdir trees are left in place.

SEE ALSO
	llm-context, llm-sessions (consume this outdir)
